OL,6,FThe heard Morrison contacted police on
OL,7,Fthe morning the car was recovered and
OL,8,Freported it had been stolen. It was
OL,9,Fregistered to his partner.
OL,11,FMcConway was arrested two days later
OL,12,Fand subsequently made a full admission
OL,13,Fto police he and Morrison had spent
OL,14,Fthe night of the attempted robbery
OL,15,Fplaying darts and drinking at a local
OL,16,Fpub. They then went home, where they
OL,17,Fcontinued to drink and took cocaine.
