OL,6,FIn a statement read to the court by
OL,7,Fprosecutor James Hartson, the victim
OL,8,Fsaid the incident initially left her
OL,9,Ffeeling frightened and anxious, but
OL,10,Fshe later became angry and questioned
OL,11,Fwhy it happened to her.
OL,13,FShe added she would not let the
OL,14,Fexperience "break" her or change her
OL,15,Fopinion of Swansea, where she had come
OL,16,Fto study medicine.
