OL,6,FDefending McConway, who has no
OL,7,Fprevious convictions, Andrew Evans
OL,8,Fsaid he had held down a responsible
OL,9,Fjob until his cocaine use became an
OL,10,Fissue, adding demotion at work and the
OL,11,Fend of a relationship had caused his
OL,12,Flife to go on a "downward trajectory."
OL,14,FMr Evans said his client had reflected
OL,15,Fon his behaviour whilst on remand and
OL,16,Fhoped to "salvage something" from the
OL,17,Fdamage caused to his own life and
OL,18,Fothers lives too.
