OL,4,Cwhile threatening her with hammer
OL,6,FJudge Huw Rees said a number of
OL,7,Faggravating factors meant the
OL,8,Fappropriate sentence would be five
OL,9,Fyears in prison. He reduced it to 54
OL,10,Fmonths due to the fact it was an
OL,11,Fattempted robbery, as well as
OL,12,Fminimising the sentence by a third to
OL,13,Faccount for the defendants' guilty
OL,14,Fpleas.
OL,16,FIn total Morrison and McConway will
OL,17,Fboth serve three years in prison,
OL,18,Fspending up to half of it in custody
OL,19,Fbefore being released on licence to
OL,20,Fserve the rest in the community.
